articles.author: Julia Musto
articles.title: US research finds 1 in 10 adults get long COVID after omicron - Fox News
articles.description: A National Institutes Health study published Thursday of American adults found that one in 10 people are getting long COVID after suffering an omicron infection.
articles.content: A new study from the National Institutes of Health found that one in 10 people are getting long COVID after suffering an omicron infection a lower estimate than earlier on in the COVID-19 pandemic. … [+2425 chars]
